{"key":"processedPost-8514740","value":{"id":8514740,"first":8513375,"last":8514993,"when":1213287940,"utime":"06/12/08 07:25 PM","content":"The dish soap is a wetting agent that also helps pasteurize the straw.<br /><br />You'll want to add some verm to your mix to prevent the bagged cow manure from turning to mud.&nbsp; In fact, I'd mix the manure and verm together before adding to the straw.<br /><br />Don't use lime in substrate.&nbsp; Mushroom mycelium prefers a slightly acidic substrate.&nbsp; Lime is for casing mix.&nbsp; I'd also leave the oil out, or at least cut the amount in half.<br />RR","title":"Re: Bulk recipe?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}